    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-07-20T09:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-07-20T09:30:00-05:00" n="96"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                <head>96. Memorandum of Conversation<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d96fn1"
                        >Source: National Archives, Nixon Presidential Materials, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 489, President’s Trip Files,
                            <persName corresp="#p_DAF1">Dobrynin</persName>/<persName
                            corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>, 1970, Vol. 1 [Part 1]. Top
                        Secret; Sensitive; Eyes Only. The meeting, which took place in the Map Room
                        at the White House, was requested by <persName corresp="#p_DAF1"
                            >Dobrynin</persName>. On July 21 <persName corresp="#p_KHA1"
                            >Kissinger</persName> sent Nixon a copy of the memorandum of
                        conversation as an attachment to a summary of his conversation with
                            <persName corresp="#p_DAF1">Dobrynin</persName>. (Ibid.) The full text
                        of the memorandum of conversation is printed in <ref
                            target="frus1969-76v12#d183">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1969–1976, volume XII, Soviet
                            Union, January 1969–October 1970, Document 183</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1970-07-20T10:30:00-04:00"
                            >July 20, 1970, 10:30 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_DAF1">Anatoliy Dobrynin</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion unrelated to <gloss target="#t_SALT1"
                    >SALT</gloss>.]</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <gloss target="#t_SALT1">SALT</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_DAF1">Dobrynin</persName> then turned the conversation to
                        <gloss target="#t_SALT1">SALT</gloss>. He said that we had not yet presented
                    our formal proposals and he wondered when they could expect them. I replied that
                    they would have them certainly the next day, but they would be along the lines
                    foreshadowed in my recent conversation.<note n="2" xml:id="d96fn2">See <ref
                            target="#d93">Document 93</ref>.</note> He said he recognized that we
                    would not split off <gloss target="#t_ABM1">ABM</gloss>s as a separate agreement
                    and asked about the accidental war question. I told him that <persName
                        corresp="#p_SGC1">Smith</persName> was under instructions not to split off
                    anything, but that I would be willing to explore with him separating out of the
                    accidental war question those issues which concerned only our two countries,
                    such as unauthorized launches of missiles or mass flights of bombers, from
                    issues that affected third countries, such as the note <persName
                        corresp="#p_SV1">Semyonov</persName> had handed to <persName
                        corresp="#p_SGC1">Smith</persName> at a concert.<note n="3" xml:id="d96fn3"
                        >See <ref target="#d91">Document 91</ref>.</note> I stated that there might
                    be a possibility of a limited technical agreement along these lines, but that
                        <persName corresp="#p_SGC1">Smith</persName> was not authorized to negotiate
                    it. This would have to be done between <persName corresp="#p_DAF1"
                        >Dobrynin</persName> and me. <persName corresp="#p_DAF1">Dobrynin</persName>
                    said he would come back to me on that.</p>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion unrelated to <gloss target="#t_SALT1"
                    >SALT</gloss>.]</p>
            </div>
